casadi::SundialsInterface Class Referenceabstract

#include <sundials_interface.hpp>

Detailed Description


Input scheme: casadi::IntegratorInput (INTEGRATOR_NUM_IN = 7)
Full nameShortDescription
INTEGRATOR_X0x0Differential state at the initial time.
INTEGRATOR_Z0z0Initial guess for the algebraic variable at the initial time.
INTEGRATOR_PpParameters.
INTEGRATOR_UuPiecewise constant control, a new control interval starts at each output time.
INTEGRATOR_ADJ_XFadj_xfAdjoint seeds corresponding to the states at the output times.
INTEGRATOR_ADJ_ZFadj_zfAdjoint seeds corresponding to the algebraic variables at the output times.
INTEGRATOR_ADJ_QFadj_qfAdjoint seeds corresponding to the quadratures at the output times.

Output scheme: casadi::IntegratorOutput (INTEGRATOR_NUM_OUT = 7)
Full nameShortDescription
INTEGRATOR_XFxfDifferential state at all output times.
INTEGRATOR_ZFzfAlgebraic variable at all output times.
INTEGRATOR_QFqfQuadrature state at all output times.
INTEGRATOR_ADJ_X0adj_x0Adjoint sensitivities corresponding to the initial state.
INTEGRATOR_ADJ_Z0adj_z0Adjoint sensitivities corresponding to the algebraic variable guess.
INTEGRATOR_ADJ_Padj_pAdjoint sensitivities corresponding to the parameter vector.
INTEGRATOR_ADJ_Uadj_uAdjoint sensitivities corresponding to the control vector.


List of available options
IdTypeDescriptionUsed in
abstolOT_DOUBLEAbsolute tolerence for the IVP solutioncasadi::SundialsInterface
ad_weightOT_DOUBLEWeighting factor for derivative calculation.When there is an option of either using forward or reverse mode directional derivatives, the condition ad_weight*nf<=(1-ad_weight)*na is used where nf and na are estimates of the number of forward/reverse mode directional derivatives needed. By default, ad_weight is calculated automatically, but this can be overridden by setting this option. In particular, 0 means forcing forward mode and 1 forcing reverse mode. Leave unset for (class specific) heuristics.casadi::FunctionInternal
ad_weight_spOT_DOUBLEWeighting factor for sparsity pattern calculation calculation.Overrides default behavior. Set to 0 and 1 to force forward and reverse mode respectively. Cf. option "ad_weight". When set to -1, sparsity is completely ignored and dense matrices are used.casadi::FunctionInternal
always_inlineOT_BOOLForce inlining.casadi::FunctionInternal

jac_penaltyOT_DOUBLEWhen requested for a number of forward/reverse directions, it may be cheaper to compute first the full jacobian and then multiply with seeds, rather than obtain the requested directions in a straightforward manner. Casadi uses a heuristic to decide which is cheaper. A high value of 'jac_penalty' makes it less likely for the heurstic to chose the full Jacobian strategy. The special value -1 indicates never to use the full Jacobian strategycasadi::FunctionInternal

365  }
366 
367  // Backwards integration, if needed
368  if (nrx_ > 0) {
369  // Take rx0, rz0, rp past the last grid point
370  if (rx0) rx0 += nrx_ * nt();
371  if (rz0) rz0 += nrz_ * nt();
372  if (rp) rp += nrp_ * nt();
373  if (uq) uq += nuq_ * nt();
374  // Next stop time due to step change in input
375  k_stop = nt();
376  // Reset the solver
377  resetB(m);
378  // Any adjoint seed so far?
379  bool any_impulse = false;
380  // Integrate backward
381  for (m->k = nt(); m->k-- > 0; ) {
382  m->t = tout_[m->k];
383  // Add impulse to backwards integration
384  if (rx0) rx0 -= nrx_;
385  if (rz0) rz0 -= nrz_;
386  if (rp) rp -= nrp_;
387  if (uq) uq -= nuq_;
388  if (u) u -= nu_;
389  if (!all_zero(rx0, nrx_) || !all_zero(rz0, nrz_) || !all_zero(rp, nrp_)) {
390  if (verbose_) casadi_message("Impulse from adjoint seeds at output time " + str(m->k));
391  impulseB(m, rx0, rz0, rp);
392  any_impulse = true;
393  }
394  // Next output time, or beginning
395  casadi_int k_next = m->k - 1;
396  m->t_next = k_next < 0 ? t0_ : tout_[k_next];
397  // Update integrator stopping time
398  if (k_next < k_stop) k_stop = next_stopB(m->k, u);
399  m->t_stop = k_stop < 0 ? t0_ : tout_[k_stop];
400  // Proceed to the previous time point or t0
401  if (any_impulse) {
402  if (verbose_) casadi_message("Integrating backward from output time " + str(m->k)
403  + ": t_next = " + str(m->t_next) + ", t_stop = " + str(m->t_stop));
404  if (m->k > 0) {
405  retreat(m, u, 0, 0, uq);
406  } else {
407  retreat(m, u, rx, rq, uq);
408  }
409  } else {
410  if (verbose_) casadi_message("No adjoint seeds from output time " + str(m->k)
411  + ": t_next = " + str(m->t_next) + ", t_stop = " + str(m->t_stop));
412  casadi_clear(uq, nuq_);
413  if (m->k == 0) {
414  casadi_clear(rx, nrx_);
415  casadi_clear(rq, nrq_);
416  }
417  }
418  }
419  // uq should contain the contribution from the grid point, not cumulative
420  if (uq) {
421  for (m->k = 0; m->k < nt() - 1; ++m->k) {
422  casadi_axpy(nuq_, -1., uq + nuq_, uq);
423  uq += nuq_;
424  }
425  }
426  }
427 
428  // Collect oracle statistics
429  join_results(m);
430 
431  // Print integrator statistics
432  if (print_stats_) print_stats(m);
433 
434  return 0;
435 }

1483  for (auto&& e2 : e1) e2 = vec(e2);
1484  }
1485  // Assemble input argument
1486  v.clear();
1487  for (casadi_int k = 0; k < ret_in_split.size(); ++k) {
1488  v.push_back(ret_in_split.at(k));
1489  for (casadi_int d = 0; d < nadj; ++d) {
1490  v.push_back(aug_in_split[d].at(k));
1491  }
1492  }
1493  integrator_in[i] = reshape(vertcat(v), aug_int.size_in(i));
1494  }
1495  std::vector<MX> integrator_out = aug_int(integrator_in);
1496 
1497  // Collect adjoint sensitivites
1498  std::vector<MX> ret_out;
1499  ret_out.reserve(INTEGRATOR_NUM_IN);
1500  for (casadi_int i = 0; i < INTEGRATOR_NUM_IN; ++i) {
1501  casadi_int j = adjmap_out(i);
1502  // Split return by grid points and sensitivities
1503  casadi_int n_grid = grid_out(j) ? nt() : 1;
1504  std::vector<casadi_int> offset = {0};
1505  for (casadi_int k = 0; k < n_grid; ++k) {
1506  offset.push_back(offset.back() + numel_out(j) / n_grid);
1507  for (casadi_int d = 0; d < nadj; ++d) {
1508  offset.push_back(offset.back() + numel_in(i) / n_grid);
1509  }
1510  }
1511  std::vector<MX> integrator_out_split = vertsplit(vec(integrator_out[j]), offset);
1512  // Collect sensitivity blocks in the right order
1513  std::vector<MX> ret_out_split;
1514  ret_out_split.reserve(n_grid * nadj);
1515  for (casadi_int d = 0; d < nadj; ++d) {
1516  for (casadi_int k = 0; k < n_grid; ++k) {
1517  ret_out_split.push_back(reshape(integrator_out_split.at((nadj + 1) * k + d + 1),
1518  size1_in(i), size2_in(i) / n_grid));
1519  }
1520  }
1521  ret_out.push_back(horzcat(ret_out_split));
1522  }
1523 
1524  Dict options = opts;
1525  options["allow_duplicate_io_names"] = true;
1526 
1527  // Create derivative function and return
1528  return Function(name, ret_in, ret_out, inames, onames, options);
1529 }

155  max_krylov_ = op.second;
156  } else if (op.first=="newton_scheme") {
157  newton_scheme = op.second.to_string();
158  } else if (op.first=="linear_solver") {
159  linear_solver_ = op.second.to_string();
160  } else if (op.first=="linear_solver_options") {
161  linear_solver_options_ = op.second;
162  } else if (op.first=="quad_err_con") {
163  quad_err_con_ = op.second;
164  } else if (op.first=="interpolation_type") {
165  interpolation_type = op.second.to_string();
166  } else if (op.first=="steps_per_checkpoint") {
167  steps_per_checkpoint_ = op.second;
168  } else if (op.first=="disable_internal_warnings") {
169  disable_internal_warnings_ = op.second;
170  } else if (op.first=="max_multistep_order") {
171  max_multistep_order_ = op.second;
172  } else if (op.first=="second_order_correction") {
173  second_order_correction_ = op.second;
174  } else if (op.first=="step0") {
175  step0_ = op.second;
176  } else if (op.first=="max_step_size") {
177  max_step_size_ = op.second;
178  } else if (op.first=="max_order") {
179  max_order_ = op.second;
180  } else if (op.first=="nonlin_conv_coeff") {
181  nonlin_conv_coeff_ = op.second;
182  } else if (op.first=="scale_abstol") {
183  scale_abstol_ = op.second;
184  }
185  }
186 
187  // Type of Newton scheme
188  if (newton_scheme=="direct") {
189  newton_scheme_ = SD_DIRECT;
190  } else if (newton_scheme=="gmres") {
191  newton_scheme_ = SD_GMRES;
192  } else if (newton_scheme=="bcgstab") {
193  newton_scheme_ = SD_BCGSTAB;
194  } else if (newton_scheme=="tfqmr") {
195  newton_scheme_ = SD_TFQMR;
196  } else {
197  casadi_error("Unknown Newton scheme: " + newton_scheme);
198  }
199 
200  // Interpolation_type
201  if (interpolation_type=="hermite") {
202  interp_ = SD_HERMITE;
203  } else if (interpolation_type=="polynomial") {
204  interp_ = SD_POLYNOMIAL;
205  } else {
206  casadi_error("Unknown interpolation type: " + interpolation_type);
207  }
208 
209  // If derivative, use Jacobian from non-augmented system if possible
210  SundialsInterface* d = 0;
211  if (nfwd_ > 0 && !derivative_of_.is_null()) {
212  d = derivative_of_.get<SundialsInterface>();
213  casadi_assert_dev(d != nullptr);
214  }
215 
216  // Get Jacobian function, forward problem
217  Function jacF;
218  Sparsity jacF_sp;
219  if (d == 0) {
220  // New Jacobian function
221  jacF = create_function("jacF", {"t", "x", "z", "p", "u"},
222  {"jac:ode:x", "jac:alg:x", "jac:ode:z", "jac:alg:z"});
223  jacF_sp = jacF.sparsity_out(JACF_ODE_X) + Sparsity::diag(nx1_);
224  if (nz_ > 0) {
225  jacF_sp = horzcat(vertcat(jacF_sp, jacF.sparsity_out(JACF_ALG_X)),
226  vertcat(jacF.sparsity_out(JACF_ODE_Z), jacF.sparsity_out(JACF_ALG_Z)));
227  }
228  } else {
229  // Reuse existing Jacobian function
230  jacF = d->get_function("jacF");
231  set_function(jacF, jacF.name(), true);
232  linsolF_ = d->linsolF_;
233  jacF_sp = linsolF_.sparsity();
234  }
235  alloc_w(jacF_sp.nnz(), true); // jacF
236 
237  // Linear solver for forward problem
238  if (linsolF_.is_null()) {
239  linsolF_ = Linsol("linsolF", linear_solver_, jacF_sp, linear_solver_options_);
240  }
241 
242  // Allocate work vectors
243  alloc_w(np_, true); // p
244  alloc_w(nu_, true); // u
245  alloc_w(nrp_, true); // rp
246  alloc_w(2 * std::max(nx_ + nz_, nrx_ + nrz_), true); // v1, v2
247 
248  // Attach functions to calculate DAE and quadrature RHS all-at-once
249  if (nfwd_ > 0) {
250  create_forward("daeF", nfwd_);
251  if (nq_ > 0) create_forward("quadF", nfwd_);
252  if (nadj_ > 0) {
253  create_forward("daeB", nfwd_);
254  if (nrq_ > 0 || nuq_ > 0) create_forward("quadB", nfwd_);
255  }
256  }
257 
258  // Attach functions for jacobian information, foward problem
259  if (newton_scheme_ != SD_DIRECT || (nfwd_ > 0 && second_order_correction_)) {
260  create_function("jtimesF", {"t", "x", "z", "p", "u", "fwd:x", "fwd:z"},
261  {"fwd:ode", "fwd:alg"});
262  if (nfwd_ > 0) {
263  create_forward("jtimesF", nfwd_);
264  }
265  }
266 
267 
268  // For Jacobian calculation
269  alloc_w(jacF.nnz_out(JACF_ODE_X), true); // jac_ode_x
270  alloc_w(jacF.nnz_out(JACF_ALG_X), true); // jac_alg_x
271  alloc_w(jacF.nnz_out(JACF_ODE_Z), true); // jac_ode_z
272  alloc_w(jacF.nnz_out(JACF_ALG_Z), true); // jac_alg_z
273 
274  // Transposing the Jacobian (for calculating jacB)
275  // This will be unnecessary once linsolF_ is used for both forward and adjoint
276  // cf. #3047
277  alloc_w(nx_ + nz_); // casadi_trans
278  alloc_iw(nx_ + nz_); // casadi_trans
279 }
